# ================================================================
# Rhombohedral Bi treated as a semiconductor
# 2x2x2 grid, defined by hand, using time-reversal
# symmetry to lower the number of k points to 3.
# The applicable symmetries have been defined by hand

# Test for Abinit: PAW + spin-orbit (zero-magnetization and non-collinear)
# Low cut-off for test
# ================================================================

# === Datasets
ndtset 2 jdtset 1 3
nspden1 1  nspinor1 1  pawspnorb1 0 ! no magnetism, no spin-orbit
#nspden2 1  nspinor2 2  pawspnorb2 1 ! spin-orbit, zero-magnetization !Temporary desactivated
nspden3 4  nspinor3 2  pawspnorb3 1 ! spin-orbit, non-collinear magnetism
prtwf1  1 prtwf2  0 prtwf3  0
getwfk1 0 getwfk2 1 getwfk3 1

# === Structure and cell
natom 2 ntypat 1 typat 2*1
znucl  83.
spinat 0 0 1  0 1 0
xred   3*0.231d0
       3*-0.231d0
acell  3*9.
angdeg 3*57.25
nband1 15 nband 30

# === SCF cycle options
nstep 20  tolvrs 1.d-7
ecut 5. pawecutdg 10.

# === K-points and syms
nkpt 3
kpt  1/4  1/4  1/4
    -1/4  1/4  1/4
     1/4 -1/4  1/4
wtk  1/4  1/4  1/2
nsym 2 nsym3 1
symrel 1 0 0  0 1 0  0 0 1
       1 0 0  0 0 1  0 1 0

# === Other options
prtden 0  prteig 0  prtwf 0
optforces 2
